S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Locator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Application schemas must describe how the associated file is identified. The associated file will commonly be named in a file reference co-attribute of the same complex attribute. Each DCEG must specify requirements for the format of the associated file and the semantics of file locator. For example, the value of file locator may be an HTML ID in an HTML file, line number in a text file) or a bookmark in a PDF file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the fixed horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Variable Factor
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The factor to be applied to the variable component of an uncertainty equation so as to provide the best estimate of the variable horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Virtual AIS Aid to Navigation Type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A purpose of a virtual AIS Aid to Navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: North Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the north side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: East Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the east side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: South Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the south side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: West Cardinal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that it should be passed to the west side of the aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Port Lateral
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the port boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Starboard Lateral
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates the starboard boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Port
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage, the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified port-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Preferred Channel to Starboard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the conventional direction of buoyage, the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified starboard-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Isolated Danger
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used alone to indicate a dangerous reef or shoal. The mark may be passed on either hand.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Safe Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Indicates that there is navigable water around the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Special Purpose
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A special purpose aid is primarily used to indicate an area or feature, the nature of which is apparent from reference to a chart, Sailing Directions or Notice to Mariners

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: New Danger Marking
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mark used to indicate the existence of a recently identified new danger, such as a wreck.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Aton Commissioning
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The process of deploying and activating a new Aid to Navigation (AtoN), ensuring that it is properly installed and operational.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Aton Removal
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The process of decommissioning and physically removing an AtoN from its designated location, either temporarily or permanently.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Aton Replacement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The act of swapping an existing AtoN with a new or upgraded unit, either due to maintenance needs or technological improvements.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Fixed Aton Change
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Modifications or updates to fixed AtoNs, such as lighthouses or beacons, which are permanently positioned.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Moire Effect
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A short range (up to 2km) type of directional light. Sodium lighting gives a yellow background to a screen on which a vertical black line will be seen by an observer on the centre line.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Orientation Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The angular distance measured from true north to the major axis of the feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Floating Aton Change
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Adjustments or replacements related to floating AtoNs, such as buoys, which are anchored but can move with water currents.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Seasonal Action Required
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Indicates whether specific actions or maintenance must be performed based on the season (for example, repositioning, removal, or other adjustments).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Audible Signal Aton Change
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Any modification to an AtoN that uses sound signals, such as foghorns or bells, to assist in navigation under low visibility conditions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The indication of an element of a signal sequence being a period of light/sound or eclipse/silence.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lit/Sound
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The indication of an element of a signal sequence being a period of light or sound.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Eclipsed/Silent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The indication of an element of a signal sequence being a period of eclipse or silence.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The earliest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date Start should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date Start indicates the earliest date of an event or the start of a date range. It is used to indicate the start of a fixed date range, the start of a periodic date range, or the deployment or implementation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The latest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date End should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date End indicates the latest date of an event or the end of a date range. It is used to indicate the end of a fixed date range, the end of a periodic date range, or the removal or cancellation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Lighted Aton Change
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Updates or modifications to light-emitting AtoNs, including changing light characteristics, intensity, or operational status.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Front leading/range light Light range reduced
Rear leading/range light Light range reduced
Front leading/range light is operating properly
Rear leading/range light is operating properly
Front leading/range beacon restored to normal
Rear leading/range beacon restored to normal

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A non-formatted digital text string.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Should be used, for example, to hold the information that is for short cautionary or explanatory notes. Therefore, text populated in text must not exceed 300 characters. Text may be in English, or in a national language. No formatting of text is possible within text. If formatted text, or text strings exceeding 300 characters, is required, then an alternate concept should be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Headline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Line Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector line length specifies the displayed length of the line, in ground units, defining the limit of the sector.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Signal Duration
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time occupied by a single instance of light/sound or eclipse/silence in a signal sequence.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Bearing
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A sector is the part of a circle between two straight lines drawn from the centre to the circumference. Sector bearing specifies the limit of the sector.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The values given to the common limits of adjacent sectors should be identical. The orientation of bearing is from seaward to the central object. This conforms with the method used in 'List of Lights' publications. A generic term such as 'to shore' cannot be used; a specific bearing must be encoded. Where a light sector limit is defined as 'to the shore', it should be encoded using a value that ensures that, when the limit is drawn, it will fall entirely on land.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Wave Length Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The distance between two successive peaks (or other points of identical phase) on an electromagnetic wave.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar Band
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The band code character of the electromagnetic spectrum within which radar wave lengths lie.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Number of Features
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a co-located group.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Multiplicity Known
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The number of features of identical character that exist as a co-located group is or is not known.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Sector Arc Extension
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An indication that the default radius of a sector arc is to be extended by 5mm.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced text file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Electronic Aton Change
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Modifications to electronic or digital AtoNs, such as AIS (Automatic Identification System) AtoNs, virtual AtoNs, or remote-controlled systems.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category Of Association
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: named associations between two or more aids to navigation and/or navigationally relevant features

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category Of Aggregation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: named aggregations between two or more aids to navigation and/or navigationally relevant features

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: MMSI Code
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The Maritime Mobile Service Identity (MMSI) Code is formed of a series of nine digits which are transmitted over the radio path in order to uniquely identify ship stations, ship earth stations,coast stations, coast earth stations, and group calls. These identities are formed in such a way that the identity or part thereof can be used by telephone and telex subscribers connected to the general telecommunications network principally to call ships automatically.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category Of Installation Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of fixed installation buoy

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: catenary anchor leg mooring (CALM)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: incorporates a large buoy which remains on the surface at all times and is moored by 4 or more anchors. Mooring hawsers and cargo hoses lead from a turntable on top of the buoy, so that the buoy does not turn as the ship swings to wind and stream.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: catenary anchor leg mooring (CALM)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mooring structure used by tankers to load and unload in port approaches or in offshore oil and gas fields. The size of the structure can vary between a large mooring buoy and a manned floating structure. Also known as single point mooring (SPM)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A signal light that shows continuously, in any given direction, with constant luminous intensity and colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly shorter than the total duration of darkness and all the appearances of light are of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Long-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A single-flashing light in which an appearance of light of not less than two seconds duration is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are repeated at a rate of not less than 50 flashes per minutes but less than 80 flashes per minutes. It may be: - Continuous quick-flashing: A quick-flashing light in which a flash is regularly repeated. - Group quick-flashing: A quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Very Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are repeated at a rate of not less than 80 flashes per minute but less than 160 flashes per minute. It may be:- Continuous very quick-flashing: A very quick-flashing light in which a flash is regularly repeated.- Group very quick-flashing: A very quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Continuous Ultra Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which flashes are regularly repeated at a rate of not less than 160 flashes per minute.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Isophased
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light with all durations of light and darkness equal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly longer than the total duration of darkness and all the eclipses are of equal duration. It may be: - Single-occulting: An occulting light in which an eclipse is regularly repeated. - Group-occulting: An occulting light in which a group of two or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated. - Composite group-occulting: An occulting light in which a sequence of groups of one or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated, and the groups comprise different numbers of eclipses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Interrupted Quick Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A quick light in which the sequence of flashes is interrupted by regularly repeated eclipses of constant and long duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Interrupted Very Quick Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light in which the very rapid alterations of light and darkness are interrupted at regular intervals by eclipses of long duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Interrupted Ultra Quick-Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light in which the ultra quick flashes (160 or more per minute) are interrupted at regular intervals by eclipses of long duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Morse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which appearances of light of two clearly different durations are grouped to represent a character or characters in the Morse code.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flash and Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a flashing light is combined with a long-flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting and Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which an occulting light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a long-flashing light of higher luminous intensity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occulting Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating light in which the total duration of light in each period is clearly longer than the total duration of darkness and in which the intervals of darkness (occultations) are all of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Long-Flash Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating single-flashing light in which an appearance of light of not less than two seconds duration is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flash Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alternating rhythmic light in which the total duration of light in a period is clearly shorter than the total duration of darkness and all the appearances of light are of equal duration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Group Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Occulting light in which the occultations are combined in groups, each group including the same number of occultations, and in which the groups are repeated at regular intervals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Very Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of very quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ultra Quick-Flash Plus Long-Flash
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a group of ultra quick flashes is followed by one or more long flashes in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Alternating
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A signal light that shows continuously, in any given direction, two or more colours in a regularly repeated sequence with a regular periodicity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fixed and Alternating Flashing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rhythmic light in which a fixed light is combined with a flashing light of higher luminous intensity and different colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: group-occulting light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An occulting light in which a group of two or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: composite group-occulting light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An occulting light in which a sequence of groups of one or more eclipses, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated, and the groups comprise different numbers of eclipses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: group flashing light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A flashing light in which a group of flashes, specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: composite group-flashing light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A light similar to a group-flashing light except that successive groups in a period have different numbers of flashes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: group quick light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: group very quick light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A very quick-flashing light in which a group of two or more flashes, which are specified in number, is regularly repeated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Interoperability Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A common unique identifier for entities which describe a single real-world feature, and which is used to identify instances of the feature in end-user systems where the feature may be included in multiple data product types.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The individual name of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum scale at which the feature may be used for example for ECDIS presentation.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The modulus of the scale is indicated, that is 1:1 250 000 is encoded as 1250000.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The production date of the source; for example the date of measurement.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Source
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The publication, document, or reference work from which information comes or is acquired.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: May be populated with the corresponding paper chart Notice to Mariners numbers, although other references are permitted.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Pictorial Representation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced picture file.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The 'pictorial representation' could be a drawing or a photo. The string encodes the file name of an external graphic file (pixel/vector).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Installation Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The date when an item was installed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Navigation Line
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of route guidance given to vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clearing Line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A straight line that marks the boundary between a safe and a dangerous area or that passes clear of a navigational danger.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Transit Line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A line passing through one or more fixed marks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Leading Line Bearing a Recommended Track
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A line passing through one or more clearly defined objects, along the path of which a vessel can approach safely up to a certain distance off.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Based On Fixed Marks
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A straight route (known as a recommended track, range or leading line), which comprises: a. at least two structures (usually beacons or daymarks) and/or natural features, which may carry lights and/or top-marks. The structures/features are positioned so that when observed to be in line, a vessel can follow a known bearing with safety. (Adapted from International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA Aids to Navigation Guide, 1990); or b. a single structure or natural feature, which may carry lights and/or a topmark, and a specified bearing which can be followed with safety. (S-57 Edition 3.1, Appendix A Chapter 2, Page 2.72, November 2000, as amended).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Depth Range Minimum Value
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum (shoalest) value of a depth range.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Where the area dries, the value is negative.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Maximal Permitted Draught
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximal permitted draught of a vessel or convoy according to the particular article/clause of the applicable law/regulation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Quality of Vertical Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reliability of the value of a sounding.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Depth Known
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth from the chart datum to the seabed (or to the top of a drying feature) is known.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Depth or Least Depth Unknown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth from chart datum to the seabed, or the shoalest depth of the feature is unknown.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Doubtful Sounding
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A depth that may be less than indicated.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unreliable Sounding
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A depth that is considered to be an unreliable value.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No Bottom Found at Value Shown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Upon investigation the bottom was not found at this depth.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Least Depth Known
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The shoalest depth over a feature is of known value.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Least Depth Unknown, Safe Clearance at Value Shown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The least depth over a feature is unknown, but there is considered to be safe clearance at this depth.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Value Reported (Not Surveyed)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Depth value obtained from a report, but not fully surveyed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Value Reported (Not Confirmed)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Depth value obtained from a report, which it has not been possible to confirm.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Maintained Depth
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth at which a channel is kept by human influence, usually by dredging.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not Regularly Maintained
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Depths may be altered by human influence, but will not be routinely maintained.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Status
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The condition of an object at a given instant in time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Permanent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Intended to last or function indefinitely.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Occasional
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Acting on special occasions; happening irregularly.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Recommended
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Presented as worthy of confidence, acceptance, use, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not in Use
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Use has ceased, but the facility still exists intact; disused.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Periodic/Intermittent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Recurring at intervals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reserved
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Set apart for some specific use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Temporary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Meant to last only for a time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Private
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Administered by an individual or corporation, rather than a State or a public body.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mandatory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Compulsory; enforced.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Extinguished
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: No longer lit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Illuminated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Lit by flood lights, strip lights, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Historic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Famous in history; of historical interest.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Public
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Belonging to, available to, used or shared by, the community as a whole and not restricted to private use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Synchronized
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Occur at a time, coincide in point of time, be contemporary or simultaneous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Watched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Looked at or observed over a period of time especially so as to be aware of any movement or change.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unwatched
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Usually automatic in operation, without any permanently-stationed personnel to superintend it.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Existence Doubtful
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A feature that has been reported but has not been definitely determined to exist.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: On Request
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: When you ask for it.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drop Away
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: To become lower in level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rising
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: To become higher in level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Increasing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Becoming larger in magnitude.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Decreasing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Becoming smaller in magnitude.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Strong
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not easily broken or destroyed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Good
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: In a satisfactory condition to use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Moderately
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Fairly but not very.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Poor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not as good as it could be or should.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Marked by buoys.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fully Operational
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Entire observation platform is operating in accordance with, or exceeding, manufacturer specifications.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Partially Operational
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: At least one instrument that is part of an observation platform is not operating to manufacturer specification.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drifting
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Floating platform at the mercy of environmental elements, whether intentional or not.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Broken
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Fractured or in pieces.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Offline
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Observation platform is intentionally not reporting an environmental observation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Discontinued
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Observation station, suite of instruments, or an individual instrument, for a particular location, has been removed and is no longer at the particular location.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Manual Observation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Observations made by a human observer.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unknown Status
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Status of an observation platform, suite of instruments, or individual instrument is not known or unspecified.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Confirmed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Made certain as to truth, accuracy, validity, availability, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Candidate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item selected for an action.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Under Modification
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item that is in the process of being modified.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Under Removal / Deletion
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item in the process of being removed or deleted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Removed / Deleted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item that has been removed or deleted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Candidate for Modification
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Item selected for modification.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: IsSlatted
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A flag or attribute indicating whether an object has slats, which are flat, narrow strips of material, often used for ventilation or design.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Accuracy
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The degree to which a vertical measurement is accurate, typically referring to the accuracy of an object's position in the vertical plane (height or depth)

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Peak Intensity
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The maximum luminous intensity of a light during its flash cycle.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Technique of Vertical Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Survey method used to obtain depth information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Echo Sounder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was measured by using an instrument that determines depth of water by measuring the time interval between emission of a sonic or ultrasonic signal and return of its echo from the bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Side Scan Sonar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was computed from a record produced by active sonar in which fixed acoustic beams are directed into the water perpendicularly to the direction of travel to scan the seabed and generate a record of the seabed configuration.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Multi Beam
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was measured by using a wide swath echo sounder that uses multiple beams to measure depths directly below and transverse to the ship's track.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Diver
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by a person skilled in the practice of diving.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Lead Line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was measured by using a line, graduated with attached marks and fastened to a sounding lead.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swept by Wire-Drag
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area was determined to be free from navigational dangers to a certain depth by towing a buoyed wire at the desired depth by two launches, or a least depth was identified using the same technique.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Laser
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using an instrument that measures distance by emitting timed pulses of laser light and measuring the time between emission and reception of the reflected pulses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swept by Vertical Acoustic System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area has been swept using a system comprised of multiple echo sounder transducers attached to booms deployed from the survey vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Electromagnetic Sensor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using an instrument that compares electromagnetic signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Photogrammetry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The science or art of obtaining reliable measurements from photographs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Satellite Imagery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using instruments placed aboard an artificial satellite.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by Levelling
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was determined by using levelling techniques to find the elevation of the point relative to a datum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swept by Side Scan Sonar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area was determined to be free from navigational dangers to a certain depth by towing a side scan sonar.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Computer Generated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The sounding was determined from a bottom model constructed using a computer.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Found by LIDAR
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The depth was measured by using an instrument that measures distance by emitting timed pulses of laser light and measuring the time between emission and reception of the reflected pulses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Synthetic Aperture Radar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A radar with a synthetic aperture antenna which is composed of a large number of elementary transducing elements. The signals are electronically combined into a resulting signal equivalent to that of a single antenna of a given aperture in a given direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hyperspectral Imagery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term used to describe the imagery derived from subdividing the electromagnetic spectrum into very narrow bandwidths. These narrow bandwidths may be combined with or subtracted from each other in various ways to form images useful in precise terrain or target analysis.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mechanically Swept
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The given area was determined to be free from navigational dangers to a certain depth by towing a line or object below the surface at the desired depth; or least depth(s) and position(s) within an area was identified using the same technique.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Traffic Flow
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Direction of vessels passing a reference point.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Inbound
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Traffic flow in a general direction toward a port or similar destination.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Outbound
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Traffic flow in a general direction away from a port or similar point of origin.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: One-Way
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Traffic flow in one general direction only.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Two-Way
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Traffic flow in two generally opposite directions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Datum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The reference level used for expressing the vertical measurements of points on the earth's surface. Also called datum level, reference plane, levelling datum, datum for sounding reduction, datum for heights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the low waters of spring tides. This level is used as a tidal datum in some areas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Lower Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of lower low water springs at a place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the surface of the sea at a tide station for all stages of the tide over a 19-year period, usually determined from hourly height readings measured from a fixed predetermined reference level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest tide observed at a place, or somewhat lower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level conforming to the lowest water level observed at a place at spring tides during a period of time shorter than 19 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Low Water Springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Indian Spring Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary tidal datum approximating the level of the mean of the lower low water at spring tides. It was first used in waters surrounding India.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean low water springs (MLWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Lowest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Lowest Astronomical Tide (LAT).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nearly Lowest Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the lowest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the Indian Spring Low Water (ISLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Lower Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the lower low waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Low Water (MLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Lower Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Lower Low Water (MLLW).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of all high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of the high waters of spring tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest level reached at a place by the water surface in one oscillation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate Mean Sea Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, usually within 0.3m from that of Mean Sea Level (MSL).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: High Water Springs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level, approximating that of mean high water springs (MHWS).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Higher High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average height of higher high waters at a place over a 19-year period.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Equinoctial Spring Low Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The level of low water springs near the time of an equinox.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lowest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The lowest tide level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary datum defined by a local harbour authority, from which levels and tidal heights are measured by this authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: International Great Lakes Datum 1985
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical reference system with its zero based on the mean water level at Rimouski/Pointe-au-Pre, Quebec, over the period 1970 to 1988.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mean Water Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of all hourly water levels over the available period of record.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lower Low Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the lowest low waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Higher High Water Large Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The average of the highest high waters, one from each of 19 years of observations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Nearly Highest High Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arbitrary level approximating the highest water level observed at a place, usually equivalent to the high water springs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Astronomical Tide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The highest tidal level which can be predicted to occur under average meteorological conditions and under any combination of astronomical conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Low Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Low water reference level of the local area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local High Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: High water reference level of the local area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Mean Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Mean water reference level of the local area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Equivalent Height of Water (German GlW)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A low water level which is the result of a defined low water discharge - called "equivalent discharge".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Shipping Height of Water (German HSW)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Upper limit of water levels where navigation is allowed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reference Low Water Level According to Danube Commission
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The water level at a discharge, which is exceeded 94 % of the year within a period of 30 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Highest Shipping Height of Water According to Danube Commission
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The water level at a discharge, which is exceeded 1% of the year within a period of 30 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dutch River Low Water Reference Level (OLR)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The water level at a discharge, which is exceeded 95% of the year within a period of 20 years.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Russian Project Water Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Conditional low water level with established probability.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Russian Normal Backwater Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Highest water level derived from the upper backwater stream in watercourse or reservoir under the normal operational conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ohio River Datum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The Ohio River datum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dutch High Water Reference Level
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Dutch High Water Reference Level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Baltic Sea Chart Datum 2000
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The datum refers to each Baltic country's realization of the European Vertical Reference System (EVRS) with land-uplift epoch 2000, which is connected to the Normaal Amsterdams Peil (NAP).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dutch Estuary Low Water Reference Level (OLW)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Dutch Estuary Low Water Reference Level (OLW)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: International Great Lakes Datum 2020
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The 2020 update to the International Great Lakes Datum, the official reference system used to measure water level heights in the Great Lakes, connecting channels, and the St. Lawrence River system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sea Floor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The bottom of the ocean and seas where there is a generally smooth gentle gradient. Also referred to as sea bed (sometimes seabed or sea-bed), and sea bottom.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sea Surface
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A two-dimensional (in the horizontal plane) field representing the air-sea interface, with high-frequency fluctuations such as wind waves and swell, but not astronomical tides, filtered out.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hydrographic Zero
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical reference near the lowest astronomical tide (LAT), below which the sea level falls only very exceptionally.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: AtoN Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifier from a list of Aids to Navigation publication, such as List of Lights.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Buoy Shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The principal shape and/or design of a buoy.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The principal shapes are those recommended in the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA System.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Conical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has approximately the shape or the appearance of a pointed cone with the point upwards.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Can
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the shape of a cylinder, or a truncated cone that approximates to a cylinder, with a flat end uppermost.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spherical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Shaped like a sphere, which is a body the surface of which is at all points equidistant from the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pillar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure is a narrow vertical structure, pillar or lattice tower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the form of a pole, or of a very long cylinder, floating upright.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Barrel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the form of a barrel or cylinder floating horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Superbuoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A very large buoy designed to carry a signal light of high luminous intensity at a high elevation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Buoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specially constructed shuttle shaped buoy which is used in ice conditions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Colour
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The property possessed by an object of producing different sensations on the eye as a result of the way it reflects or emits light.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: White
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The achromatic object colour of greatest lightness characteristically perceived to belong to objects that reflect diffusely nearly all incident energy throughout the visible spectrum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Black
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The achromatic color of least lightness characteristically perceived to belong to objects that neither reflect nor transmit light.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Red
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A color whose hue resembles that of blood or of the ruby or is that of the long-wave extreme of the visible spectrum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Green
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Of the color green.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Blue
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A color whose hue is that of the clear sky or that of the portion of the color spectrum lying between green and violet.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Yellow
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A color whose hue resembles that of ripe lemons or sunflowers or is that of the portion of the spectrum lying between green and orange.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Grey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Of the color grey.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Brown
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors between red and yellow in hue, of medium to low lightness, and of moderate to low saturation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Amber
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A variable color averaging a dark orange yellow.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Violet
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors of reddish-blue hue, low lightness, and medium saturation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Orange
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors that are between red and yellow in hue.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Magenta
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A deep purplish red.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pink
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any of a group of colors bluish red to red in hue, of medium to high lightness, and of low to moderate saturation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category Of Synthetic AIS Aid To Navigation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A classification of AIS AtoNs that are transmitted electronically and linked to a real-world object but do not physically exist at the broadcast location.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category Of Physical AIS Aid To Navigation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A classification of AIS AtoNs that correspond to an actual, physical Aid to Navigation at a real-world location.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Physical AIS Type 1
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Simple transmission of static, pre-programmed information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Physical AIS Type 2
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Transmission of dynamic, real-time updated information via connected sensors.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Physical AIS Type 3
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Full two-way communication including transmission, remote control and configuration

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Colour Pattern
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A regular repeated design containing more than one colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Horizontal Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vertical Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented vertically.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Diagonal Stripes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented diagonally (that is, not horizontally or vertically).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Squared
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Often referred to as checker plate, where alternate colours are used to create squares similar to a chess or draught board. The pattern may be straight or diagonal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stripes (Direction Unknown)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Straight bands or stripes of differing colours oriented in an unknown direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Border Stripe
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A band or stripe of colour which is displayed around the outer edge of the feature, which may also form a border to an inner pattern or plain colour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Single Colour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: One solid colour of uniform coverage.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rectangle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A four-sided shape that is made up of two pairs of parallel lines and that has four right angles, on a different coloured background.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A shape that is made up of three lines and three angles, on a different coloured background.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Radar Conspicuous
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A feature which returns a strong radar echo.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Marks Navigational - System Of
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The system of navigational buoyage a region complies with.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA A
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA A system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: IALA B
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA B system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: No System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids do not conform to any defined system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Other System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to a defined system other than International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Main European Inland Waterway Marking System
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids as required in international, national or regional regulations that contain the same navigational aids as the European Code for Inland Waterways of UNECE, or if there is no regulation for a waterway, navigational aids as recommended in the European Code for Inland Waterways of UNECE

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Russian Inland Waterway Regulations
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the Russian inland waterway regulations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Brazilian National Inland Waterway Regulation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the Brazilian national inland waterway regulation

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Paraguay-Parana Waterway - Brazilian Complementary Aids
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Navigational aids conform to the Brazilian complementary aids on the Paraguay-Parana waterway.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nature of Construction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The building's primary construction material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Masonry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed of stones or bricks, usually quarried, shaped, and mortared.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Concreted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed of concrete, a material made of sand and gravel that is united by cement into a hardened mass used for roads, foundations, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Loose Boulders
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from large stones or blocks of concrete, often placed loosely for protection against waves or water turbulence.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hard Surfaced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed with a surface of hard material, usually a term applied to roads surfaced with asphalt or concrete.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unsurfaced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed with no extra protection, usually a term applied to roads not surfaced with a hard material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wooden
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from wood.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Metal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from metal.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Glass Reinforced Plastic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from a plastic material strengthened with fibres of glass.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Painted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The application of paint to some other construction or natural feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Framework
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from a lattice framework of, often diagonal, intersecting struts.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Latticed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure of crossed wooden or metal strips usually arranged to form a diagonal pattern of open spaces between the strips.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Glass
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: [1] Any artificial or natural substance having similar properties and composition, as fused borax, obsidian, or the like. [2] Something made of such a substance, as a windowpane.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Fiberglass
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from fiberglass.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Plastic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Constructed from plastic.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Type of Buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Type equipment used as a buoy in a particular installation.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Types of light buoy; for example LANBY-100, LS-35, LL-30, LL-28, LL-26, LL-26(M), LL-24, LS-24, LSP-24, LT-10Types of buoy e.g. U-17C(P), U-17S(P), U-17C(S), U-17S(S), UR-17C(P), UR-17S(P), UR-17C(S), UR-17.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Beacon Shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Describes the characteristic geometric form of the beacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stake, Pole, Perch, Post
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An elongated wood or metal pole, driven into the ground or seabed, which serves as a navigational aid or a support for a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Withy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tree without roots stuck or spoiled into the bottom of the sea to serve as a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A solid structure of the order of 10 metres in height used as a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lattice Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure consisting of strips of metal or wood crossed or interlaced to form a structure to serve as an aid to navigation or as a support for an aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pile Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A long heavy timber(s) or section(s) of steel, wood, concrete, etc., forced into the seabed to serve as an aid to navigation or as a support for an aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cairn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mound of stones, usually conical or pyramidal, raised as a landmark or to designate a point of importance in surveying.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoyant Beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tall spar-like beacon fitted with a permanently submerged buoyancy chamber, the lower end of the body is secured to seabed sinker either by a flexible joint or by a cable under tension.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Visual Prominence
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The extent to which a feature, either natural or artificial, is visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Visually Conspicuous
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Term applied to an object either natural or artificial which is distinctly and notably visible from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Not Visually Conspicuous
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An object that may be visible from seaward, but cannot be used as a fixing mark and is not conspicuous.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Prominent
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Objects which are easily identifiable, but do not justify being classed as conspicuous.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Height
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The value of the vertical distance to the highest point of the feature, measured from a specified vertical datum.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Height must not be used for floating objects.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Vertical Length
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The total vertical length of a feature.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: For floating objects: the vertical distance from the surface of water to the highest point of that object. For fixed objects: the vertical distance from seabed or ground to the highest point of that object. For objects on top of other objects: the vertical distance from the lowest to the highest point of that object. Vertical length measurements do not require a datum.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of Landmark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of prominent cultural and natural features in the landscape.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cairn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mound of stones, usually conical or pyramidal, raised as a landmark or to designate a point of importance in surveying.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cemetery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A site and associated structures devoted to the burial of the dead.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chimney
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vertical structure containing a passage or flue for discharging smoke and gases of combustion.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dish Aerial
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A parabolic aerial for the receipt and transmission of high frequency radio signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flagstaff
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A staff or pole on which flags are raised.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Flare Stack
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tall structure used for burning-off waste oil or gas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mast
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A relatively tall structure usually held vertical by guy lines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Windsock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tapered fabric sleeve mounted so as to catch and swing with the wind, thus indicating the wind direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Monument
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure erected and/or maintained as a memorial to a person and/or event.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Column/Pillar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A cylindrical or slightly tapering body of considerably greater length than diameter erected vertically.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Memorial Plaque
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A slab of metal, usually ornamented, erected as a memorial to a person or event.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Obelisk
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tapering shaft usually of stone or concrete, square or rectangular in section, with a pyramidal apex.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Statue
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A representation of a living being, sculptured, moulded, or cast in a variety of materials (for example: marble, metal, or plaster).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cross
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A monument, or other structure in form of a cross.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dome
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A landmark comprising a hemispherical or spheroidal shaped structure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radar Scanner
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A device used for directing a radar beam through a search pattern.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A relatively tall, narrow structure that may either stand alone or may form part of another structure.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Windmill
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system of vanes attached to a tower and driven by wind (excluding wind turbines).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Windmotor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A modern structure for the use of wind power.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spire/Minaret
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tall conical or pyramid-shaped structure often built on the roof or tower of a building, especially a church or mosque.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Large Rock or Boulder on Land
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An isolated rocky formation or a single large stone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Triangulation Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A recoverable point on the earth, whose geographic position has been determined by angular methods with geodetic instruments. A triangulation point is a selected point, which has been marked with a station mark, or it is a conspicuous natural or artificial feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boundary Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A marker identifying the location of a surveyed boundary line.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observation Wheel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Wheels with passenger cars mounted external to the rim and independently rotated by electric motors.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Torii
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A form of decorative gateway or portal, consisting of two upright wooden posts connected at the top by two horizontal crosspieces, commonly found at the entrance to Shinto temples.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (1) An elevated structure extending across or over the weather deck of a vessel, or part of such a structure. The term is sometimes modified to indicate the intended use, such as navigating bridge or signal bridge. (2) A structure erected over a depression or an obstacle such as a body of water, railroad, etc., to provide a roadway for vehicles or pedestrians.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dam
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A barrier to check or confine anything in motion; particularly one constructed to hold back water and raise its level to form a reservoir, or to prevent flooding.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Function
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A specific role that describes a feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Harbour-Masters Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A local official who has charge of mooring and berthing of vessels, collecting harbour fees, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Customs Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Serves as a government office where customs duties are collected, the flow of goods are regulated and restrictions enforced, and shipments or vehicles are cleared for entering or leaving a country.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Health Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The office which is charged with the administration of health laws and sanitary inspections.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hospital
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An institution or establishment providing medical or surgical treatment for the ill or wounded.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Post Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The public department, agency or organisation responsible primarily for the collection, transmission and distribution of mail.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Hotel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An establishment, especially of a comfortable or luxurious kind, where paying visitors are provided with accommodation, meals and other services.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Railway Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building with platforms where trains arrive, load, discharge and depart.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Police Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The headquarters of a local police force and that is where those under arrest are first charged.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Water-Police Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The headquarters of a local water-police force.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pilot Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The office or headquarters of pilots; the place where the services of a pilot may be obtained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pilot Lookout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A distinctive structure or place on shore from which personnel keep watch upon events at sea or along the coast.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bank Office
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An office for custody, deposit, loan, exchange or issue of money.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Headquarters for District Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The quarters of an executive officer (director, manager, etc.) with responsibility for an administrative area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Transit Shed/Warehouse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or part of a building for storage of wares or goods.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Factory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or buildings with equipment for manufacturing; a workshop.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Power Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A stationary plant containing apparatus for large scale conversion of some form of energy (such as hydraulic, steam, chemical or nuclear energy) into electrical energy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Administrative
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for the management of affairs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Educational Facility
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An establishment for teaching and learning (for example school, college, university, etc).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Church
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Christian worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chapel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place for Christian worship other than a parish, cathedral or church, especially one attached to a private house or institution.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Temple
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Jewish worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pagoda
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A Hindu or Buddhist temple or sacred building.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shinto Shrine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Shinto worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buddhist Temple
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building for public Buddhist worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Mosque
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A Muslim place of worship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Marabout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A shrine marking the burial place of a Muslim holy man.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Lookout
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Keeping a watch upon events at sea or along the coast.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Communication
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Transmitting and/or receiving electronic communication signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Television
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A system for reproducing on a screen visual images transmitted (usually with sound) by radio signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radio
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Transmitting and/or receiving radio-frequency electromagnetic waves as a means of communication.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Radar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A method, system or technique of using beamed, reflected, and timed radio waves for detecting, locating, or tracking objects, and for measuring altitudes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Light Support
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A structure serving as a support for one or more lights.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Microwave
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Broadcasting and receiving signals using microwaves.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cooling
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Generation of chilled liquid and/or gas for cooling purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A place from which the surroundings can be observed but at which a watch is not habitually maintained.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Timeball
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A visual time signal in the form of a ball.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Clock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Instrument for measuring time and recording hours.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Used to control the flow of traffic within a specified range of an installation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Airship Mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Equipment or structure to secure an airship.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stadium
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An arena for holding and viewing events.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bus Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building where buses and coaches regularly stop to take on and/or let off passengers, especially for long-distance travel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Passenger Terminal Building
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building within a terminal for the loading and unloading of passengers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sea Rescue Control
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A unit responsible for promoting efficient organization of search and rescue services and for coordinating the conduct of search and rescue operations within a search and rescue region.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Observatory
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building designed and equipped for making observations of astronomical, meteorological, or other natural phenomena.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ore Crusher
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or structure used to crush ore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Boathouse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A building or shed, usually built partly over water, for sheltering a boat or boats.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Pumping Station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A facility to move solids, liquids or gases by means of pressure or suction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Roof Above Navigable Water
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A roof that is extending above navigable water, e.g. to protect open cargo holds from rain during loading and unloading. Depending on the vertical clearance vessels can pass under the roof above navigable water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Building Above Navigable Water
